<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-content">

    <img
      class="hero-logo"
      src="/images/amiibo-vault-logo.png"
      alt="Amiibo Vault logo"
    >

    <p class="eyebrow">Your personal collector space</p>

    <h1>Amiibo Vault</h1>

    <p class="hero-tagline">
      Discover amiibo, build your wishlist, and keep track of your
      personal collection in one place.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="primary-button" href="/amiibos">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass"></i>
        Browse Amiibos
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="feature-section">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Everything in one vault</p>
    <h2>Built for amiibo collectors</h2>

    <p>
      Amiibo Vault provides a simple way to discover characters and
      organize the amiibo that you own or hope to collect.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="feature-grid">

    <article class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass"></i>
      </div>

      <h3>Discover</h3>

      <p>
        Browse amiibo from multiple characters, game series, and
        collectible types.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon wishlist-color">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-star"></i>
      </div>

      <h3>Build a Wishlist</h3>

      <p>
        Mark the amiibo that you hope to add to your collection in
        the future.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon collection-color">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-heart"></i>
      </div>

      <h3>Track Your Collection</h3>

      <p>
        Save the amiibo that you own and view your personal collection
        from one account.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon review-color">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-comment"></i>
      </div>

      <h3>Share Reviews</h3>

      <p>
        Rate and review the amiibo in your collection during a later
        project phase.
      </p>
    </article>

  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-callout">
  <div>
    <p class="eyebrow">Open the vault</p>
    <h2>Start exploring the collection</h2>

    <p>
      Search through the available amiibo and identify the ones that
      belong on your shelf.
    </p>
  </div>

  <a class="secondary-button" href="/amiibos">
    View the Library
    <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i>
  </a>
</section>